{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, we observed that shelf editing was never expressed by \"Biologists\".",
    "Customizations [T3].",
    "For making customizations, such as a change of color encoding, NLI was most often referred to as the sensible choice.",
    "For example, the specifications would be \"very straightforward to translate\" or \"cosmetic changes seem to be suitable for code inputs\" (P6, P8).",
    "Code was preferred because of the support for fine-grained control, e.g., by tweaking \"the exact hex color code\" (P10)."
  ]
}